<HEADLINE>
1st LD Writethru: 16 killed in road accident in NW Pakistan
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
ISLAMABAD, June 21 (Xinhua)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least 16 people including three children and one woman were killed and three
others injured in a serious road accident which took place Monday morning on
Indus Highway near Karak city in Pakistan's northwest province of Khyber
Pakhtunkhwa, according to local sources and media reports.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy happened when a coach heading from Rawalpindi, a garrison city of
Pakistan's capital Islamabad, to Bannu district in northwest Pakistan collided
with a trailer on Indus Highway near Shanu Ghandi district in Karak city in
northwest Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The dead and injured were pulled out of the seriously damaged coach after rescue
workers cut open the coach, said local sources, adding that the trailer's driver
fled the scene after the accident.
</P>
<P>
The injured people are being rushed to a hospital in the area, sources said.
</P>
